anches of time were marked out as properly without work: childhood and retirement. Accessible, wide-ranging and occasionally polemical, this book provides the first history of how we have imagined and used time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aLeisurexSocial aspectszEnglandxHistory. 0aTimexSocial aspectszEnglandxHistory. 0aWorkxSocial aspectszEnglandxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  achildhood.  agender.  aleisure.  aretirement.  atime.  awork-life balance.  awork.1 aCunningham, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packagez978311128357940uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611229340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526112293423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526112293/original  a978-3-11-128357-9  Manchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packageb2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles